config AUFSNG_FS
	tristate "aufs-ng filesystem support (AUFS-compatible union filesystem)"
	select FS_STACK
	default n
	help
	  aufs-ng is a standalone, from-scratch union filesystem
	  compatible with many live Linux distributions. It registers
	  as filesystem type
	  "aufs", using AUFS's own mount option syntax and on-disk
	  whiteout format, so that scripts issuing real AUFS
	  mount/remount commands work unmodified.

	  A live-boot sequence typically needs this filesystem type
	  mounted before any loadable module can be reached (the same
	  reason AUFS and overlayfs are usually built statically), so
	  this option should be built in ("Y"), not built as a loadable
	  module, wherever that applies. Say Y if you are building a
	  live-distro kernel that needs it; say N otherwise.
